-- Adaptive Penalty Method --

This project contains an implementation of the Adaptive Penalty Method, or
shortly APM, proposed by H.J.C. Barbosa and A.C.C. Lemonge in 2003 which is
used by evolutionary algorithms when solving constrained optimization problems.  

More information about APM can be found in the following references:

Helio J.C. Barbosa and Afonso C.C. Lemonge, 
A new adaptive penalty scheme for genetic algorithms, 
Information Sciences, Volume 156, Issues 3–4, 15 November 2003, Pages 215-251.
(http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0020025503001774)

Lemonge, A. C. C. and Barbosa, H. J. C. (2004), 
An adaptive penalty scheme for genetic algorithms in structural optimization. 
International Journal for Numerical Methods in Engineering, 59: 703–736. 
doi: 10.1002/nme.899

